  "text": "The Liberty Mutual psychophysical tables were used to evaluate the physical demands on the jobs of 6912 workers in 5 different industries. [CITATION_1] A significant negative correlation (p Ͻ .05) was found between overexertion injury incidence rates and psychophysical ''percentage capable'' rating for the most stressful task on these jobs (i.e., as percentage capable increased, injury rates decreased). Similar to the study described in the previous paragraph, [CITATION_2] there was a background level of overexertion injuries that could not be attributed to physical demands.",
